Port Elizabeth police have opened an enquiry docket after finding three bales containing 180kg  of dagga on the N2 near the Addo Road onramp on Monday morning. Police spokesperson Colonel Priscilla Naidu said  members of the SAPS Algoa Park were patrolling the area when they noticed the three bales lying in the road just after 5am. “[P]olice stopped and picked up three huge bales  suspected to have fallen off a moving vehicle,” Naidu said. She said on opening the 60kg bales, they  found each contained dagga.  The origin and destination of the dagga is unknown. — HeraldLIVE